text:
Study DataPipe and update my Stroop test to save result data to OSF.

Follow the instructions and do these.


Create an OSF account and a new project on it
Create a DataPipe account and link it to my OSF account by using an OSF token
Create a new experiment on DataPipe and configurate it


Update my stroop.html to send data

    /* save data with DataPipe */
    const subject_id = jsPsych.randomization.randomID(10);
    const filename = `${subject_id}.csv`;

    const save_data = {
      type: jsPsychPipe,
      action: "save",
      experiment_id: "478JTfm2S8zr",
      filename: filename,
      data_string: ()=&gt;jsPsych.data.get().csv()
    };            

    timeline.push(save_data);
The Stroop Test is ready for sending data to my OSF project.
